<td width="10"><img src="http://www.maximumeq.com/forum/Images/SmallNew.gif" border="0" alt="New Message"></td><td width="50%"><font face="Verdana" size="1" color="EEEEEE"><b>Group loot policy (modified 0 times)</b> </font></td><td width="50%" align="RIGHT"><font face="Verdana" size="1" color="EEEEEE"><b>Snowhawk</b></font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
<td><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="CENTER">
<tr>
<td><a href="UltraBoard.cgi?Action=ShowProfile&ID=snowhawk&Board=general&Idle=30&Sort=0&Order=Descend&Page=0&Session=" target="Profile" OnMouseOver="window.status='View Snowhawk (snowhawk) Profile.';return true;" OnMouseOut="window.status=''"><font face="Verdana" size="1" color="000000 ">Profile</font></a></td><td align="RIGHT"></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="EEEEEE">
<td><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="5" cellpadding="5" align="CENTER">
<tr>
<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">Just a little something for me to whine about that has always peeved me- randoms. Example--I've hunted in Cazic Thule for about 2 levels(in Dalnir now though). My favorite spot was always Tae. I camped it maybe 7 or 8 times there for about 4 hours each, with all different groups. I saw 3 cloaks drop. I was the only one in the group who needed one to wear TWICE, and all three times they insisted on randoming it. Naturally, I lost. I ended up paying an exorbitant 600 for mine, FROM A GROUP MEMBER. Another example-- same thing, Cazic Thule. Everytime Ravenscale dropped, whether or not the rogue needed it, everyone randomed. I, personally, have a problem with this. Starting at about level 50, the person that needs it gets the item. That's all there is to it. Why, I ask you, should it be different at lower levels? I'm sick of losing randoms to casters who are just going to sit on their butts in commons and auction to sell it! It's not right! I don't random unless it's an item I need. (Except I did random on the RS to give it to the rogue if I won), and I don't think it's fair policy to do otherwise. What kind of mentality, I ask, do people have? One thing in particular is this: Casters- tanks, in general, need more items and spend more money than you. This is a fact, accept it. After a point, spells are cheap, and casters simply have less equipment(and generally cheaper) to choose from. Tank equipment will always cost more than caster items. Why, then, would you cheat tanks out of cash? An example- adamantite epolets, for clerics, are as good as it gets until pretty high levels, and they go for what, 75? Rangers go through maybe 5 different shoulders(PW, Banded, BS Mantle, Crested spaulders, Tattered Mantle) til they get to 50, most of which cost more. Average ranger spends maybe 3.5k on shoulders by 45. Average cleric? 75-150 for the epolets. Get the point?<br>
     Let me finish by saying I don't wish to offend or stereotype casters at all. This is merely a rant and what I observe being commonly practiced. I'm sure there are exceptions out there.<br>
     Anyways, sorry to rant :)<hr>"Swift as wind, powerful as lightning, steadfast as the oak- I am ranger." Snowhawk</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
