<td><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="5" cellpadding="5" align="CENTER">
<tr>
<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">Im sorry but I personally believe the item should go to the person in the group who can use it, even if the others in the group have alt. characters that can use it. If no one in the group can use it then everyone roll for it. This is a game about adventuring and having fun, if you plan on joining a group to kill something just to get the item to sell off, then you should let the group know. That way every one knows what they are getting into and for what.<br>
Several of my friends will start groups and let them know off the bat they are raiding the mob for a certain item and that the first one that drops is his, but he usually groups with good friends who just want to help him out, and he lets the rest of the group take all the other drops from the other mobs they kill without taking a plat. So overall it will be fair<br>
to the others and later on he will group with them to help them aquire an item that they need. So I guess it all boils down to playing style, if you need an item let the group Know before hand and if your killing the mob to harvest weapons/armor/items to sell let them all know as well. Plain and simple, if your starting the group let them know whats going on so everyone knows what to expect!!!</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
